&lt;p&gt;I’ve been looking for cheap HW solution to stream audio to a DAC I relocated far awayfrom my computer.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;All solutions I found were either too expensive or making compromises on quality. 
My Maverick Audio DAC has an toslink input that was previously connected to the digital output of my computer.
&lt;img src=&quot;/images/maverick_front.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Maverick Front&quot; /&gt;
&lt;img src=&quot;/images/maverick_back.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Maverick Back&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I thought about buying an 2e generation Apple TV (with toslink output) but streaming to it using Airplay is limited to 44kHz/16 bit streams…
The WR320 Wireless WIFI Audio Receiver seems to be a good and cheap solution at 56€. It has an optical out but it seems to require some specific apps for configuration  and streaming…(&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.amazon.fr/Récepteur-Audio-Wi-Fi-Multiroom-Bluetooth/dp/B01LY9U439/ref=sr_1_1?__mk_fr_FR=ÅMÅŽÕÑ&amp;amp;keywords=wr320&amp;amp;qid=1579816386&amp;amp;s=electronics&amp;amp;sr=1-1&quot;&gt;amazon&lt;/a&gt;) same for the Yamaha AWXAD10DGY at 124€ (&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.amazon.fr/dp/B0713NRK5R?tag=georiot-fr-default-21&amp;amp;th=1&amp;amp;psc=1&amp;amp;ascsubtag=t3-5300575664297264317-21&quot;&gt;amazon&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;At the end I decided to order a Raspberry Pi Zero W and a JustBoom Digi Zero pHAT. At about 62€ (including a 16GB microsd), this solution is more expensive than the WR320 but I will be able to recycle this hardware to other uses if needed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/images/pizerowh.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Pi Zero&quot; height=&quot;200px&quot; /&gt; &lt;img src=&quot;/images/PHAT.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Maverick Back&quot; height=&quot;200px&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

